history.text: Hello
Hi. Have you seen the movie, The Blind Side?
No. What is it about?
It is based off a book. It is about Michael Oher who played football for the Baltimore Ravens.
I don't follow football. What's so special about his story?
It's not really a football movie. It is his about him when he was younger. He came from an impoverished neighborhood and is taken in and adopted by a new family.
Sounds interesting. Who is in it?
Sandra Bullock and Tim McGraw play the part of the parents who take him in.
Who plays him?
He is played by Quinton Aaron. I don't know if he's been in anything else.
What's it rated?
Rotten Tomatoes gave it a 6.1 out of 10. Metacritic gave it 53/100 and CinemaScore gave it an A+.
Sounds good. Is it in the theaters now?
No, it is actually from 2009. I watch it every time it is on TV.
PG13?
I'm not sure.
Okay for kids?
I think so. There is some talk about drugs because of his mother's addiction. I think it has a really positive meaning though.
Did it win any awards?
I don't remember. The critics praised Sandra Bullock's performance though.
I do like her. I don't think I've seen Tim McGraw in anything though.
I don't know if I ever have either. Jae Head plays the little brother and Lily Collins plays the sister but I don't know if they have been in anything else either.
It is directed by John Lee Hancock.
Don't recognize those names either. Which is fine. If somebody says something is good I'l check it out no matter who is in it.
It is one of those movies that if it is on I watch it. I think it is a great story.
How long is it?
I would guess about 2 hours.
Do you watch a lot of movies?
Sometimes. It really depends. What about you? What types of movies do you like?
I pretty much like all kinds. True stories are some of my favorites though.
I would definitely recommend The Blind Side then.
I will definitely check it out. Not sure how I missed it.
Enjoy!

uid2response.feedback: The movie sounds like my kind of movie and I am interested in seeing if it lives up to user 2's comments
